<task id="R2-012" project="SprkChat Platform Enhancement R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Multi-Document Context — Shared 30K Token Budget Across Document Sets with Proportional Allocation</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai</tags>
    <estimated-effort>medium</estimated-effort>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF API code implementation — extends DocumentContextService with multi-document overload; implements proportional budget allocation and cross-document chunk ranking; supports FR-12 (multi-document analysis)</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>[011]</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend `DocumentContextService` (created in Task R2-011) to support multi-document analysis where
    multiple document IDs share a single 30K token budget with intelligent proportional allocation.

    **New overload**:
    ```csharp
    public Task&lt;MultiDocumentContextResult&gt; InjectMultiDocumentContextAsync(
        string sessionId, IReadOnlyList&lt;string&gt; documentIds, IReadOnlyList&lt;ChatMessage&gt; chatHistory,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);
    ```

    **Budget allocation strategy**:
    1. Start with equal proportional allocation: each document gets `30K / N` tokens as its initial budget
    2. Retrieve and chunk all documents in parallel (bounded concurrency — max 5 concurrent per ADR-016)
    3. For documents smaller than their proportional share, reallocate unused tokens to other documents
       proportionally ("leftover reallocation")
    4. Apply conversation-aware chunk selection per document using the same embedding similarity approach
       from Task R2-011 (latest user message embedding → cosine similarity → select top chunks within budget)
    5. Cross-document chunk interleaving: merge selected chunks from all documents sorted by relevance
       score (not by document) so the most relevant content from any document appears first in the prompt

    **Result model**:
    ```csharp
    public record MultiDocumentContextResult(
        IReadOnlyList&lt;DocumentChunkGroup&gt; DocumentGroups,  // per-document: chunks + tokens used
        IReadOnlyList&lt;DocumentChunk&gt; MergedChunks,          // cross-document interleaved by relevance
        int TotalTokensUsed,
        bool AnyTruncated);
    ```

    **Integration**: `PlaybookChatContextProvider` should call the multi-document overload when `chatHistory`
    carries multiple document IDs in `ChatHostContext.DocumentIds`. Each document group in the system prompt
    includes a header: `[Document: {filename}]` to help the AI attribute quotes correctly.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with Azure AI and Minimal API expertise</role>

  <goal>
    `DocumentContextService` has a working multi-document overload that respects the 30K shared budget via
    proportional allocation with leftover reallocation, applies conversation-aware chunk selection per
    document, and interleaves chunks cross-document by relevance score. AI can cross-reference and compare
    across 5 documents in a single session (FR-12).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
