    <patterns>
      <pattern>Bounded parallel retrieval: `var semaphore = new SemaphoreSlim(5); await Task.WhenAll(documentIds.Select(id => ProcessWithSemaphore(id, semaphore)))` — limits to 5 concurrent SpeFileStore calls</pattern>
      <pattern>Leftover reallocation: first pass allocates N/each; collect leftover from small docs; second pass redistributes to docs still under their optimal allocation</pattern>
      <pattern>Cross-document interleaving: collect all (chunk, relevanceScore, documentIndex) tuples; sort by relevanceScore descending; take until budget exhausted</pattern>
      <pattern>Document attribution header in prompt: `\n\n[Document: {filename}]\n{chunk.Text}` — helps AI cite sources correctly in responses</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task R2-011 created single-document context injection. R2 also requires multi-document analysis
      (FR-12): users can select multiple documents from the AnalysisWorkspace file list and ask the AI
      to compare, cross-reference, or synthesize across them. The challenge is fair budget allocation —
      with 5 documents sharing 30K tokens, each gets at most 6K tokens, which may not represent long
      documents well. The leftover reallocation strategy allows short documents to donate their unused
      budget to longer ones, maximizing information density in the context window.

      Cross-document chunk interleaving is important for comparison tasks: rather than presenting all
      of document 1, then all of document 2 (which wastes early context on less-relevant content),
      interleaving by relevance score surfaces the most pertinent passages from any document first.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Strictly depends on Task R2-011 (DocumentContextService must exist first). Safe to run in parallel
      with R2-013, R2-014, R2-015 through R2-019 after R2-011 completes. Own files: updates to
      DocumentContextService.cs, new MultiDocumentContextResult.cs, updates to PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Read the completed `DocumentContextService.cs` from R2-011 to understand the single-document implementation before extending it</step>
    <step order="1">Design `MultiDocumentContextResult` and `DocumentChunkGroup` record models</step>
    <step order="2">Create `InjectMultiDocumentContextAsync` overload with the bounded parallel retrieval pattern (SemaphoreSlim max 5)</step>
    <step order="3">Implement initial proportional allocation: `perDocBudget = 30_000 / documentIds.Count`</step>
    <step order="4">Implement leftover reallocation: collect unused tokens from docs smaller than their budget and redistribute proportionally to remaining docs</step>
    <step order="5">Apply conversation-aware chunk selection per document (reuse single-doc embedding similarity logic from R2-011)</step>
    <step order="6">Implement cross-document chunk interleaving: merge all (chunk, score, docIndex) tuples, sort by score descending, enforce total budget cap</step>
    <step order="7">Add `[Document: {filename}]` attribution headers before each document's chunks in the system prompt</step>
    <step order="8">Update `PlaybookChatContextProvider` to call multi-document overload when `ChatHostContext.DocumentIds.Count &gt; 1`</step>
    <step order="9">Verify no unbounded `Task.WhenAll` — confirm SemaphoreSlim or equivalent bounding is in place</step>
    <step order="10">Run `dotnet build` — verify no errors</step>
    <step order="11">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task R2-012 status to completed (🔲 → ✅)</step>
  </steps>

